HEADWORD: Pot-au-feu
<hw>Pot`-au`-feu"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., lit.,
pot on the fire.]</ety> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>A dish of broth, meat,
and vegetables prepared by boiling in a pot, -- a dish esp. common among
the French.</def> <rj><au>Grant Allen.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

